               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Taʾammǝra Māryām “Miracles of Mary” (fols. 2ra-3va)
 I-1) Taʾammǝra
                     Māryām “Miracles of Mary” : 1 miracle (fols. 2ra-2vb)
 I-2) ʾƎsaggǝd laki
                     wa-ʾǝweddǝsaki... “I worship Thee…” (fols. 2vb-3va)
 II) Wǝddāse ʾAmlāk
                     “Praise of God” (fols. 4ra-145rb)
 II-1) Monday’s prayer of Basil of
                     Caesarea (fols. 4ra-21vb) 
 II-2) Tuesday’s prayer of Efrem the Syrian
                     (fols. 21vb-49rb) 
 II-3) Wednesday’s prayer of Efrem the Syrian (fols.
                     49va-70ra) 
 II-4) Thursday’s prayer of John Saba (ʾAragāwi Manfasawi)
                     (fols. 70ra-96ra) 
 II-5) Friday’s prayer of Shenute (fols.
                     96ra-114vb)
 II-6) Saturday’s prayer of Athanasius of Alexandria (fols.
                     114ra-129vb) 
 II-7) Sunday’s prayer of Cyril of Alexandria (fols.
                     130ra-145rb)
 III) Ṣalota nädära, ʾAsmat-prayer against a disease called
                     nädära caused by the evil eye (fols. 145rb-146rb) (cp. Ms. KTM-014, fol. 41r-
                     44r)
 IV) Ǝgziʾabǝḥer za-bǝrhānāt ʾǝgziʾabǝḥer za-śǝlṭānāt... “God of
                     Lights, God of Powers...” (fols. 146ra-147vb)
 
 Additio 1.</summary>
